I normally don't like Trevor, but this was a well-done interview. Puts all the news anchors and journalists to shame, merely by talking the facts and coyly avoiding the politics of it. However, to those watching who found this informative and enlightening, this shouldn't be news to you. I've already gotten ALL the same info shared here from the White House press conferences, multiple times. It might've come in smaller chunks over the course of a few days, but the administration and the experts and all the health agencies were working around the clock to learn and understand as much and as fast as possible as they were able, so then it was presented. Never have I been confused or misinformed about COVID-19 info being putting out there for the public. It's great that people on social media and Trevor's followers can get the info they need, but if that's the only source of one's info, then therein lies the problem. (This isn't an endorsement of the mainstream media, either; if anything they're part of the problem of misinformation considering the fear they've sowed into the populace with all the doomsday numbers they've been pushing, even though experts like Dr. Fauci have debunked them over and over again, yet the media still presents it as gospel.) Research entails not just googling or watching social media or the news or the gov't, but knowing how to discern what is reliable and true, what is BS, and everything in between, and it doesn't require being an expert either.
Be safe, but most importantly be smart, out there.
